# Example remote layout file.
#
# This is the layout `D Remote` applies (also known as `display-remote.sh`).
# Goal: BetterDisplay virtual display is the mirror master; physical display
# mirrors to it. Screens.app/VNC ends up streaming the virtual's resolution,
# which can be much smaller than the physical display.
#
# Optional directives this layout supports (lines starting with `#`):
#
#   # betterdisplay: connect-all-displays
#       Tells `display-remote.sh` that this layout uses a BetterDisplay virtual
#       display. The script will discard any stale virtual screen with the
#       create directive's --virtualScreenName, then create a fresh one
#       before applying the displayplacer command.
#
#   # betterdisplay-create: <flags>
#       Arguments passed verbatim to `betterdisplaycli create`. Required for
#       the discard/create cycle. Pin the resolution list with
#       --resolutionList=<WxH> --useResolutionList=on so the virtual display
#       defaults to your intended remote resolution.
#
# Replace this by running:
#   ../scripts/capture-layout.sh remote
#
# Or hand-edit. A working remote example for Studio Display + ScreensRemote:
#   # betterdisplay: connect-all-displays
#   # betterdisplay-create: --type=VirtualScreen --virtualScreenName=ScreensRemote --virtualScreenSerial=313775617 --virtualScreenVendorNumber=2198 --virtualScreenModelNumber=10498 --aspectWidth=16 --aspectHeight=9 --resolutionList=1920x1080 --useResolutionList=on --virtualScreenHiDPI=on
#   displayplacer "id:s313775617+s1879776955 res:1920x1080 hz:60 color_depth:4 enabled:true scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0"
displayplacer "id:your-display-id res:your-mode scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0" # PLACEHOLDER
